ENTRY            F0582   20251215   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0582001   20251215   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 10         27
TITLE      4H resonances in the d+t reaction
AUTHOR     (V.I.Grantsev,V.S.Zaritskij,V.I.Konfederatenko,
           B.V.Lashchenov,O.F.Nemets,V.A.Pilipchenko,
           O.M.Povoroznik,B.G.Struzhko)
INSTITUTE  (4UKRIJD)
REFERENCE  (J,BAS,53,(1),171,1989) English translation
           (J,IZV,53,175,1989)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4UKRIJD) U-120 cyclotron
DETECTOR   (TELES,SIBAR) Telescopes consisted of silicon neutron
            -alloyed E detectors with the thickness of 1.5 mm and
           silicon surface-barrier delta-E detectors with the
           thickness of 50-70 um were placed on two independent
           platforms: one detector at the left and the other two
           detectors at the right from the beam. Diaphragms (6 mm
           in diam.) were placed immediately in front of delta-E
           detectors at the distance of 150-200 mm from the
           target. Solid angles were tested on counting rates in
           peaks of deuteron elastic scattering on titanium,
           tritium and carbon nuclei.
SAMPLE     Tritium-titanium target with the thickness of
           2.5 ug/cm2 was used.
METHOD     (EDE,COINC)
MONITOR    (1-H-3(D,EL)1-H-3,,DA) - triton was detected.
           (1-H-3(D,N)2-HE-4,,DA)
HISTORY    (20050817C)
           (20160229A) English translation was added.
           (20251215A) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              27
COMMON               2          3
EN         E-ERR-DIG
MEV        MEV
       13.6       0.01
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           34
SUBENT        F0582002   20251215   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  7         13
REACTION   (1-H-3(D,N+P)1-H-3,,DA/DA/DE,P/T/P)
ANG-SEC    (ANG1,P)
           (ANG2,T)
PART-DET   (P,T)
EN-SEC     (E,P)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical error. Statistical errors are not
           given in the range of proton energies E < 4 MeV, since
           additional distortions are oossible in the spectrum as
           a result of energy loss in the non-sensitive layers of
           the dE and E detectors.
STATUS     (CURVE,,V.I.Grantsev+,J,BAS,53,(1),171,1989) Fig.1
HISTORY    (20251215A) SD: BIB updated. Data re-digitized.
           DATA-ERR -> ERR-S.
ENDBIB              13
